FBIS4-43678 "drweu119__a94029" FBIS-WEU-94-119-A Daily Report 21 June 1994 ANNEX Germany Deputy SPD Chairwoman Supports Red-Green Coalition Deputy SPD Chairwoman Supports Red-Green Coalition AU1706193294 Hamburg DPA in German 1803 GMT 17 Jun 94--FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY AU1706193294 Hamburg DPA German BFN [Excerpt] Lampertheim -- The Social Democratic Party of Germany's [SPD] deputy chairwoman, Heidemarie Wieczorek-Zeul has spoken out for a red-green coalition. A shift in power cannot be achieved "with the parties that are responsible for the desperate situation in Germany: Christian Democratic Union/Christian Social Union, and Free Democratic Party," she told the SPD Hesse South party conference at Lampertheim on Friday [17 June]. As far as the Bundestag election campaign is concerned, the Social Democrats must quickly draw the conclusions from their defeat at the European election, Wieczoerek-Zeul said. [passage omitted]
